frameDefinitions: An Entity aids in the successful completion of a Purpose.
An Entity meets the pre-conditions for participating in an Event.

A Factor affects the outcome of an Undertaking, which  can be a goal-oriented activity or the maintenance of a desirable state, the work in a Field, or something portrayed as affecting an Interested_party.

Commerce is a situation in which a Buyer and a Seller have agreed upon an exchange of Money and Goods (possibly after a negotiation), and then perform the exchange, optionally carrying it out with various kinds of direct payment or financing or the giving of change.
An Entity changes from a Prior_state to a Post_state in a sequence that follows a pre-defined plan, expectation, or model of change.
frameExamples: A box is an <t>ideal</t> storage device.
Conductor software gives us the hands-on <t>capability</t> to provide updates immediately
Temperature is the most <t>critical</t> factor in successful storage.
Their offensive armament has <t>developed</t> from short range missiles to long-range ballistic weaponry in a relatively short period .
